  <body>
    <section name="Request Publication">
      <span class="shortdesc">How to ask the editor to publish a document?</span>

   <script type="text/javascript">
    leftpx=300;
    bottompx=300;
   </script>
   <div class='group'>
    <div id='screenshot'><div>
      <img src="../../../../images/screenshots/cms_M13/contribs/goto_request_schedule_publication.png" alt='request schedule publication screenshot'/>
    </div></div>
    <p>
      About to request publication of the document 'multibazaar2009'.
    </p>
   </div>

   <p>
    In a document in <a href='../concepts/review_mode.html'>review mode</a>, e.g. after
    <a href='./save_document.html'>saving that document</a>,
    select the 'schedule publication (request)'
    action at the top to request that the document be published.
    <a href='./schedule_publication.html'>A window will popup</a> where you can schedule at
    what date and time you want the publication to occur.
   </p>
   <p>
    The editor will be notified and accept or reject your request.
   </p>
   <p>Note that the editor can publish or take offline documents without your request.
      See <a href='./editor_actions.html'>editor actions</a>.
   </p>

